main event: A report of a fast-moving, hovering object observed at Ent AFB, Colorado in 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be metallic and round in shape, similar to a 'penguin eraser'.
The object was observed at an approximate altitude of 3,000 feet.
The object approached from the west, hovered for approximately 1 minute over the base, then pulled straight up and out of sight at a high speed.
The report includes a photograph labeled 'Astro (star/planet)' but no human faces are visible.
The report discusses the importance of collecting physical evidence of unidentified flying objects for scientific examination.
result: Identified as an astro (star/planet) object that appeared and disappeared rapidly, checked by motion on GRADE.
photographs: Yes, one photograph labeled 'Astro (star/planet)' but no human faces visible.
